tldr: The user requested to implement a database for questionnaire responses, a
  CSV export feature, and a simple admin dashboard with authentication. The plan
  was executed, including updating demographics, creating a Prisma schema,
  implementing API routes, setting up middleware-based authentication, and
  building the admin dashboard. All core functionalities were successfully
  implemented and tested.
overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding database capabilities and an admin dashboard. The core
  intent was to store questionnaire responses, allow data retrieval (CSV
  export), and provide a secure, simple login for clients to access this data.
  The approach involved updating existing demographic fields, defining a new
  Prisma model for questionnaire responses, and building a set of API routes for
  data interaction. A key decision was to use NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma
  for database management and to implement a streamlined authentication system
  using Next.js middleware and a single admin password. After initial
  implementation, the authentication was further simplified based on user
  feedback. Extensive testing confirmed that all database operations, API
  endpoints, and the admin dashboard with its login/logout and CSV export
  features were fully functional.
